rstanding, love, and physical pleasure—and our relationships with other people. It thus has profound significance for both psychological healing and development, and for the relationship of psychotherapist and client.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aEmpathy. 0aPsychotherapy. 0aSelf. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Religion and Philosophy. 4aPsychology : Psychology. 4aPsychology : Psychotherapy. 4aPsychology : Transpersonal Psychology. 7aPSYCHOLOGY / Psychotherapy / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791479582423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791479582/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles